    {
      "id": "3364750c-f3ba-807a-aecb-ce9b4afad004",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Generalizability across different contexts is a known flaw of the current Student Performance Predictive Models. Authors present their framework and show how it would work in an online environment called CourseKata. Results show that modelability is a promising avenue for generalizability across contexts and potentially institutions. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "3364750c-f3ba-807a-aecb-ce9b4afad004",
        "parent": {
